      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_330_1791_08_31_page01.jpg"/>
            <!--filenames for photos associated with this letter. Example: <pb n="1" facs="image1.jpg image2.jpg image3.jpg"/> -->
            <opener>
               <dateline><!--If there's no date line, omit this element. Record in the order in which it is written on the letter.-->
                  <name type="place" ref="./Placeography.xml#Bristol_ENK">Princes Building<lb/>
                        Hot Wells Bristol<lb/>
                  </name>
                  <date when="1791-08-31"/>31<hi rend="superscript">st</hi> August 1791<lb/>
               </dateline>
               <salute>
                  <persName>
                            My D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Madam<lb/>
                     <!-- Use if letter has a saluation ("Dear Sir," for example). If not, delete this line.-->
                  </persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p> I this day arrived at<lb/>
                    Clifton whither your letter was<lb/>
                    sent to me - We have <del/>(<persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeE1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs.</hi>
                  <lb/>
                        E</persName>M has accompanied me) got a<lb/>
                    very neat house to ourselves<lb/>
                    &amp; are so comfortably settled, that<lb/>
                    we venture to promise you<lb/>
                    tolerable accommodation able accomodations if in<lb/>
                    your Tour you would pass some<lb/>
                    time with us.- We propose to<lb/>
                    stay here at least a month &amp;<lb/>
                    nothing could be a greater favor<lb/>
                    to us than your company.<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>Lovell appears better - &amp; though<lb/>
                    Physicians express apprehension<lb/>
                    I am inclined to think his<lb/>
                    disease is not consumptive.<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeE1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs.</hi>
               </persName> joins me in the kindest<lb/>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_330_1791_08_31_page02.jpg"/>
                    kindest compliments<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
                    I am <persName ref="./Personography.xml#DayX1">Dear Madam</persName>
               <lb/>
                    your obliged &amp; faithful<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR1">Rich<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> Lovell Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p><!--A postscript goes here, outside the <closer>. --></p>
            </postscript>
            <!--You can include a <pb/> here, or inside the postScript.-->
            <!-- Format for postscripts. 
               Postscripts do NOT go inside closer tags. Adjust to take into account the order in your letter. 
               Sometimes the signature is on page three, the address on page four, then the postscript follows back on the top of page one, for example.-->
            <closer><!--Use the <closer> element again to hold Address Leaf information.-->
               <address>
                  <addrLine>
                     <unclear>BRISTOL</unclear>
                  </addrLine>
                  <lb/>
                  <addrLine>
